While they don't have coffee service in the room, it's available down in the lobby and they even provided us with "to go" cups for our morning walk.	The decor was very "posh" it is probably liked by most that stay there but just wasn't our style, the lobby is very small and is often full so hard to move about.	We like the Vintage Park because although you are in a large city, it has the feeling of being at a country inn with the inviting fireplace and comfy overstuffed furniture in the lobby.